{
  "doc_id": "51934",
  "text": "The extracts were lyophilized, weighed and stored in sealed vials at 4 °C until use. Extraction yield (%, w/w) was calculated as the ratio of the weight of the extract to the weight of the crude plant powder (oven-dry weight). As a consequence, the standard phytochemical methods described previously [CITATION_1] were used to test for the presence of flavonoids, alkaloids, phenolic, saponins and tannins.",
